by Disney, but were not released by Marvel or Disney-Lucasfilm Press. Their canonical status is disputed due to some minor changes made to the story due to cultural interpretation but all are film adaptations.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=jenheddle |number=604430151309365249 |date=May 29, 2015 |title=@DarthSpiriah @pauldunahoo @MasterAndrew15 It is approved but its canon status is grey area. We gave them leeway for cultural interpretation |accessdate=2016-12-19}}</ref> \n\n''Star Wars: Story Before the Force Awakens'' is a [[webcomic]] adaptation of the original trilogy by Korean artist and writer Hong Jac-ga. The strips were translated to English and have been made available worldwide on [[Line Webtoon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.webtoons.com/en/sf/Star%20Wars/list?title_no=544|title=Star Wars, List1 {{!}} LINE Webtoon}}</ref> ''The Story Before the Force Awakens'' spans the \"Rise of the Empire Era\" and the \"Rebellion Era\". \n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n* ''An Old Friend'' (Issue #1) (12 BBY\u20136 BBY)\n* ''Meeting the Droids'' (Issue #2) (6 BBY\u20130 BBY)\n* ''Beginning of an Adventure'' (Issue #3) (0 BBY)\n* ''Only Hope'' (Issue #4) (0 BBY)\n* ''Escape'' (Issue #5) (0 BBY)\n* ''Death Star'' (Issue #6) (0 BBY)\n* ''Rescue'' (Issue #7) (0 BBY)\n* ''Darth Vader'' (Issue #8) (0 BBY)\n* ''Vanishing into the Force'' (Issue #9) (0 BBY)\n* ''The Little Spark'' (Issue #10) (0 BBY)\n* ''X-Wing'' (Issue #11) (0 BBY)\n* ''One Shot'' (Issue #12) (0 BBY)\n* ''Awakening of the Force'' (Issue #13) (0 BBY)\n* ''Miracle of Yavin'' (Issue #14) (0 BBY)\n{{col-3}}\n* ''Suffering'' (Issue #15) (3 ABY)\n* ''Strike'' (Issue #16) (3 ABY)\n* ''Retreat'' (Issue #17) (3 ABY)\n* ''Dagobah'' (Issue #18) (3 ABY)\n* ''Master Yoda'' (Issue #19) (3 ABY)\n* ''Training'' (Issue #20) (3 ABY)\n* ''Dark Side of Force'' (Issue #21) (3 ABY)\n* ''Calling'' (Issue #22) (3 ABY)\n* ''Trap'' (Issue #23) (3 ABY)\n* ''Unprepared Duel'' (Issue #24) (3 ABY)\n* ''The Cruel Truth'' (Issue #25) (3 ABY)\n* ''Choice'' (Issue #26) (3 ABY)\n* ''Determination'' (Issue #27) (3 ABY)\n{{col-3}}\n* ''Jabba's Palace'' (Issue #28) (4 ABY)\n* ''Pit of Carkoon'' (Issue #29) (4 ABY)\n* ''Lightsaber'' (Issue #30) (4 ABY)\n* ''Rescue'' (Issue #31) (4 ABY)\n* ''Secret of Birth'' (Issue #32) (4 ABY)\n* ''Forest Moon'' (Issue #33) (4 ABY)\n* ''Protectors of the Forest'' (Issue #34) (4 ABY)\n* ''Surrender'' (Issue #35) (4 ABY)\n* ''The Emperor'' (Issue #36) (4 ABY)\n* ''Rage'' (Issue #37) (4 ABY)\n* ''Light vs. Dark'' (Issue #38) (4 ABY)\n* ''Epiphany'' (Issue #39) (4 ABY)\n* ''The End'' (Issue #40) (4 ABY)\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Novel adaptations into manga===\n{{Main|Star Wars manga}}\nThe comics listed here are licensed by Disney, but were not released by Marvel or Disney-Lucasfilm Press. Their canonical status is disputed due to some minor changes made to the story due to cultural interpretation, but all adapt canonical novels.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=jenheddle |number=604430151309365249 |date=May 29, 2015 |title=@DarthSpiriah @pauldunahoo @MasterAndrew15 It is approved but its canon status is grey area. We gave them leeway for cultural interpretation |accessdate=2016-12-19}}</ref>\n\n====''[[Star Wars: Lost Stars]]'' (2017)====\n''Star Wars: Lost Stars'' is a webcomic adaptation of the [[Claudia Gray]] novel of the same name by Japanese artist and writer Komiyama Yuusaku. The strips debuted May 4, 2017 on the Japanese version of [[Line Webtoon]].<ref name=\"loststars\">{{cite web|title=LINE\u30de\u30f3\u30ac\u3001\u300cLINE\u30de\u30f3\u30ac\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb \u6625\u306e\u65b0\u9023\u8f097\u9023\u5f3e\u300d\u3092\u958b\u59cb|url=https://linecorp.com/ja/pr/news/ja/2017/1720|publisher=LINE |accessdate=19 April 2017}}</ref> A trade paperback will be released in December 2017, with an English translation to be released in May 2018.<ref name=\"yenpress\">{{cite web|last1=Nadine|title=Yen Press Announces a Manga Adaptation of Star Wars: Lost Stars|url=http://yenpress.com/2017/11/yen-press-announces-a-manga-adaptation-of-star-wars-lost-stars/ |publisher=Yen Press|accessdate=23 November 2017}}</ref> Spans the ''Rise of the Empire Era'', the ''Rebellion Era'', and the ''New Republic Era'', from approximately 11 years before ''Episode IV: A New Hope'' to 1 year after ''Episode VI: Return of the Jedi''.\n*Volume 1 (December 2017)\n**Prologue #1 (May 2017)\n**Prologue #2 (May 2017)\n**Issue #1 (June 2017)\n**Artwork #1 (June 2017)\n**Issue #2 (July 2017)\n**Issue #3 (July 2017)\n**Issue #4 (August 2017)\n**Issue #5 (August 2017)\n**Issue #6 (September 2017)\n**Issue #7 (September 2017)\n**Issue #8 (October 2017)\n**Issue #9 (October 2017)\n**Issue #10 (November 2017)\n**Issue #11 (November 2017)\n*Uncollected\n**Issue #12 (December 2017)\n**Artwork #2 (December 2017)\n**Issue #13 (January 2018)\n**Issue #14 (January 2018)\n**Issue #15 (February 2018)\n**Issue #16 (February 2018)\n**Issue #17 (March 2018)\n**Issue #18 (March 2018)\n**Issue #19 (April 2018)\n**Issue #20 (May 2018)\n**Issue #21 (May 2018)\n**Issue #22 (June 2018)\n**Issue #23 (July 2018)\n**Issue #24 (July 2018)\n**Issue #25 (August 2018)\n\n====''Star Wars: Leia, Princess of Alderaan'' (2018)====\n''Star Wars: Leia, Princess of Alderaan'' is a webcomic adaptation of the [[Claudia Gray]] novel of the same name by Japanese artist Komiyama Yusaku. The strips are set to debut in June 2018 on the Japanese version of [[Line Webtoon]].<ref name=\"princessofalderaan\">{{cite web|title=\u3010LINE\u30de\u30f3\u30ac\u3011\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30fb\u30a6\u30a9\u30fc\u30ba\u30b9\u30d4\u30f3\u30aa\u30d5\u5c0f\u8aac\u306e\u516c\u5f0f\u30b3\u30df\u30ab\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba\u30ec\u30fc\u30d9\u30eb\u300cLINE STAR WARS COMICS\u300d\u3092\u65b0\u305f\u306b\u8a2d\u7acb|url=https://linecorp.com/ja/pr/news/ja/2017/1984 |publisher=LINE |accessdate=10 March 2018}}</ref> Set approximately three years before ''Episode IV: A New Hope''.\n\n====''Star Wars: Lords of the Sith'' and ''Star Wars: Heir to the Jedi'' (2018)====\n''Star Wars: Lords of the Sith'' and ''Star Wars: Heir to the Jedi'' are Japanese comic adaptations of the novels by the same names. The comics were published by [[Line Webtoon]] and feature art submitted by AOKI, winner of a fan contest. Both comics have debuted in 2018.\n\n==References==\n'''Footnotes'''\n{{notelist}}\n\n'''Citations'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.darkhorse.com/Zones/StarWars/Timeline Dark Horse, publisher of most ''Star Wars'' Comics: timeline]\n* [http://starwars.wikia.com/wiki/List_of_comics List of ''Star Wars'' comic books] on [[Wookieepedia]]\n* [http://www.starwarstimeline.net/Complete%20Saga.htm The Star Wars Extended Universe Timeline]\n\n{{Star Wars}}\n{{Star Wars comics}}\n\n[[Category:Comics based on Star Wars| ]]\n[[Category:Star Wars lists|Comics]]\n[[Category:Lists of comics based on works|Star Wars]]\n[[Category:Lists of stories|Star Wars comics]]\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Star Wars comic books}}\n\n[[es:Star Wars (historieta)]]\n[[fr:Star Wars (bande dessin\u00e9e)]]\n[[hu:Star Wars k\u00e9preg\u00e9nyek list\u00e1ja]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Star Wars'' comic books}}\n{{about|graphic novels and comics|a complete list of ''Star Wars'' novels|List of Star Wars books{{!}}List of ''Star Wars'' books}}\n{{mergeto|Star Wars comics|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{original research|date=October 2016}}\n{{more citations needed|date=October 2016}}\n{{inuniverse|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n\nThis is a '''list of [[Star Wars comics]]''', [[comic books]] set in the fictional ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe. Lucasfilm's now-corporate sibling [[Marvel Comics]], which published ''Star Wars'' comics from 1977 to 1986, are once again publishing ''Star Wars'' titles that started in 2015. [[Dark Horse Comics]] owned the license to publish ''Star Wars'' comics from [[Lucasfilm]] exclusively from 1991 to 2014. Comics published prior to 2015 have been rebranded as non-canon with the designation ''[[Star Wars expanded to other media|Legends]]''.\n\n'''BBY''' stands for years before the Battle of Yavin, which occurred during the [[Star Wars (film)|original ''Star Wars'' film]].{{EpIV}} '''ABY''' stands for years after the Battle of Yavin.\n{{Inc-lit}}\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Film and television adaptations==\n{{Main|Star Wars expanded to other media}}\nAll film and television adaptations are canon except on the parts where they divert from the films.\n===Film adaptations===\n* ''[[Star Wars (1977 comic book)|Star Wars]]'' ([[Marvel Comics]]\n**1\u20136: ''[[Star Wars (film)#Merchandising|Star Wars]]'' by [[Bruce Jones (comics)|Bruce Jones]]{{efn|Also included in ''[[Classic Star Wars]]: A Long Time Ago... Volume 1: Doomworld'' by [[Archie Goodwin (comics)|Archie Goodwin]] (which collects Marvel ''Star Wars'' #1\u201320)}}\n*** ''Star Wars''\n*** ''Six Against the Galaxy''\n*** ''Death Star''\n*** ''In Battle with Darth Vader''\n*** ''Lo, the Moons of Yavin''\n*** ''Is This the Final Chapter?''\n**39\u201344: ''[[The Empire Strikes Back#Comic book adaptation|The Empire Strikes Back]]'' by [[Archie Goodwin (comics)|Archie Goodwin]]{{efn|Also included in ''Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... Volume 3: Resurrection of Evil'' (which collects Marvel's ''Star Wars'' #39\u201353)}}\n*** ''Beginning''\n*** ''Battleground: Hoth''\n*** ''Imperial Pursuit''\n*** ''To Be a Jedi''\n*** ''Betrayal at Bespin''\n*** ''Duel a Dark Lord''\n** ''[[Return of the Jedi (comic)|Return of the Jedi]]'' by Archie Goodwin\n* [[Dark Horse Comics]]\n** ''Episode I: The Phantom Menace'' by [[Henry Gilroy]]\n** ''Episode II: Attack of the Clones'' by Henry Gilroy\n** ''Episode III: Revenge of the Sith'' by Miles Lane\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!| Title\n!| Publishing Date\n!| Placement in Timeline\n!| Author\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" | Marvel\n|-\n|''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]'' #1\u20137\n|October 2018\u2013April 2019\n|13-10 BBY\n|Robbie Thompson\n|-\n|''[[Rogue One]